Dr Nuhu Milan Adeh has been elected as the Gombe State gubernatorial candidate of the Action Alliance in the forthcoming 2023 general elections. Dr Nuhu was elected during the partyâ€™s primaries on Tuesday along with 24 other contestants into the 24 constituencies of the State House of Assembly. The State party chairman, Auwal Ibrahim who made the disclosure said the party is fully ready to participate in the forthcoming general elections. According to him, all the candidates, beginning from the governorship down to the State Assembly candidates are gearing up for massive campaigns and they will be ready to confront candidates in any other party. While congratulating all the winners of the primary election, the Chairman urged the candidates not to betray the confidence reposed in them and to immediately move into the grassroots to commence mobilization of the electorates. He said, Action Alliance will be the party to beat in Gombe State during the elections because it understands the mood, feelings and sufferings of the people of Gombe State, as such, it is ready to address them and bring succour to the people.